	<h5 class="card-title">Exodus 31:12-17</h5>
	<blockquote>

		<p class="fs-5">
			<sup><b>12</b></sup>
			And 
			<WordTemplate English="Yehovah" Hebrew="יְהוָה" TransLiteration="Yehova" H="559" />
			spake unto Mosheh, saying,
		</p>

		<p class="fs-5">
			<sup><b>13</b></sup>
			Speak thou also unto 
			<WordTemplate English="the children" Hebrew="בְּנֵי" TransLiteration="benei" H="1121" />
			<WordTemplate English="of Israel" Hebrew="יִשְׂרָאֵל" TransLiteration="Yisrael" H="3478" />
			saying, Verily 
			<WordTemplate English="my sabbaths" Hebrew="שַׁבְּתֹתַי" TransLiteration="shabbetotai" H="7676" />
			<WordTemplate English="ye shall keep" Hebrew="תִּשְׁמֹרוּ" TransLiteration="tishmoru" H="8104" />
			<WordTemplate English="for it is a sign" Hebrew="אוֹת" TransLiteration="ot" H="226" />
			between me and you
			<WordTemplate English="throughout your generations" Hebrew="לְדֹרֹתֵיכֶם" TransLiteration="ledoroteichem" H="1755" />
			that ye may know that I am 
			<WordTemplate English="Yehovah" Hebrew="יְהוָה" TransLiteration="Yehova" H="559" />
			<WordTemplate English="that doth sanctify you." Hebrew="מְקַדִּשְׁכֶם" TransLiteration="mekaddishchem." H="6942" />
		</p>

		<p class="fs-5">
			<sup><b>14</b></sup>
			<WordTemplate English="Ye shall keep" Hebrew="וּשְׁמַרְתֶּם" TransLiteration="ushemartem" H="8104" />
			<WordTemplate English="the sabbath" Hebrew="הַשַּׁבָּת" TransLiteration="hashshabbat" H="7676" />
			therefore; for it is 
			<WordTemplate English="holy" Hebrew="קֹדֶשׁ" TransLiteration="kodesh" H="6944" />
			unto you: 
			every one that 
			<WordTemplate English="defileth it" Hebrew="מְחַלְלֶיהָ" TransLiteration="mechalleiha" H="2490" />
			<WordTemplate English="shall surely be" Hebrew="מוֹת" TransLiteration="mot" H="4191" />
			<WordTemplate English="put to death:" Hebrew="יוּמָת" TransLiteration="yumat" H="4191" />
			for whosoever doeth any work therein, 
			<WordTemplate English="that soul" Hebrew="הַנֶּפֶשׁ" TransLiteration="hannefesh" H="5315" />
			<WordTemplate English="shall be cut off" Hebrew="וְנִכְרְתָה" TransLiteration="venichretah" H="3772" />
			from among his people
		</p>

		<p class="fs-5">
			<sup><b>15</b></sup>
			
			Six days may work be done;
			<WordTemplate English="but in the seventh" Hebrew="הַשְּׁבִיעִי" TransLiteration="hashshevii," H="7637" />
			<WordTemplate English="[is] the sabbath" Hebrew="שַׁבַּת" TransLiteration="shabbat" H="7676" />
			<WordTemplate English="of rest" Hebrew="שַׁבָּתוֹן" TransLiteration="shabbaton" H="7677" />
			<WordTemplate English="holy" Hebrew="קֹדֶשׁ" TransLiteration="kodesh" H="6944" />
			to <WordTemplate English="Yehovah" Hebrew="לַיהוָה" TransLiteration="yehovah;" H="3068" />
			whosoever doeth any work
			<WordTemplate English="in the sabbath" Hebrew="הַשַּׁבָּת" TransLiteration="hashshabbat" H="7676" />,
			<WordTemplate English="he shall surely" Hebrew="מוֹת" TransLiteration="mot" H="4191" />
			<WordTemplate English="be put to death" Hebrew="יוּמָת" TransLiteration="yumat." H="4191" />
		</p>

		<p class="fs-5">
			<sup><b>16</b></sup>
			Wherefore the children of Israel shall keep the sabbath, 
			to observe the sabbath throughout their generations, for a perpetual covenant.
		</p>


<span class='nrl'>בְּ</span>רֵאשִׁית

		<p class="fs-5">
			<sup><b>17</b></sup>
			It is a sign between me and the children of Israel for ever: 
			for in six days <b>Yehovah</b> <span class="hebrew"> יְהֹוָה </span> made heaven and earth, 
			and on the seventh day he rested, and was refreshed.
		</p>

		<small class="float-end"><i>Shemoth</i> <span class="hebrew16">שְׁמֹות</span> <sup>Exodus </sup> 31:12-17</small>
